# No AI commit attribution

Never add any of the following to commits, PRs, or code comments:

- `Co-authored-by: Cursor` / `Co-authored-by: Cursor Agent <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
- `Made-with: Cursor` / `Made with Cursor`
- `Co-authored-by: Claude` / Claude Code generated banners
- Any `--trailer` that attributes the change to an AI agent

When creating commits, use only the subject/body you write. Do not pass git `--trailer` for attribution. Global hooks also strip these; do not work around them.
